name: Phage - m/m 01
description: Existing on a strange state between "living" and "non-living", bacteriophages (or phages) are one of the most common entities inhabiting Earth. These intracellular parasites are present on almost every environment containing bacteria, including our insides. Mostly harmless if you're not a bacteria.////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////Part of the Microfauna/Microflora series of digital illustrations focused on viruses, bacteria and other microorganisms.
